trans-unit.source: By design, QPromise is a move-only object. This behavior helps to ensure that whenever the promise is destroyed, the associated future object is notified and will not wait forever for the results to become available. However, this is inconvenient if one wants to use the same promise to report results from different threads. There is no specific way to do that at the moment, but known mechanisms exist, such as the use of smart pointers or raw pointers/references. QSharedPointer is a good default choice if you want to copy your promise and use it in multiple places simultaneously. Raw pointers or references are, in a sense, easier, and probably perform better (since there is no need to do a resource management) but may lead to dangling.

CMYK has four components, all in the range 0-255: cyan (C), magenta (M), yellow (Y) and black (K). Cyan, magenta and yellow are called subtractive colors; the CMYK color model creates color by starting with a white surface and then subtracting color by applying the appropriate components. While combining cyan, magenta and yellow gives the color black, subtracting one or more will yield any other color. When combined in various percentages, these three colors can create the entire spectrum of colors.
trans-unit.target: CMYK에는 청록색 (C), 자홍색 (M), 노랑색 (Y) 및 검은 색 (K)의 0-255 범위의 4 가지 구성 요소가 있습니다. 시안, 마젠타 및 노랑을 빼기 색상이라고합니다. CMYK 색상 모델은 흰색 표면으로 시작한 다음 적절한 구성 요소를 적용하여 색상을 빼서 색상을 만듭니다. 청록색, 자홍색 및 노란색을 결합하면 색상이 검은 색으로 바뀌고 하나 이상을 빼면 다른 색상이 만들어집니다. 이 세 가지 색상을 다양한 비율로 결합하면 전체 색상 스펙트럼을 만들 수 있습니다.

trans-unit.source: Caching is enabled for the item's logical (local) coordinate system. Rendering quality will typically degrade, depending on the resolution of the cache and the item transformation. The first time the item is redrawn, it will render itself into the cache, and the cache is then reused for every subsequent expose. The cache is also reused as the item is transformed.
